Method behavioural specifications:
- The integer list parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer list parameter `nums` must contain at least one element.
- The integer result is the minimum number of seconds needed to make all elements in the integer list `nums` equal.
- At each second, for every index `i` in the range `[0, n - 1]`, the value at index `i` is replaced with either the value at index `i`, the value at index `(i - 1 + n) % n`, or the value at index `(i + 1) % n`.
- All elements in the integer list `nums` get replaced simultaneously.